    <question>
        <prompt>The fundamentalist-modernist controversy of the 1920s centered on:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Economic policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Religious responses to social and scientific changes</option>
            <option letter="c">Political reform movements</option>
            <option letter="d">Immigration policies</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The fundamentalist-modernist controversy centered on religious responses to social and scientific changes, particularly evolution and biblical interpretation. Fundamentalists defended traditional Protestant beliefs against modernist attempts to reconcile Christianity with new scientific theories and changing social values. This conflict culminated in events like the Scopes Trial and reflected broader cultural tensions between tradition and modernity in 1920s America.</explanation>
    </question>
